836|"carpet was gone, AND SO WAS THE LAMB!"|FALSE
836|"There was a horrible silence. The Lamb--the baby, all alone--had been"|FALSE
836|"wafted away on that untrustworthy carpet, so full of holes and magic."|FALSE
836|"And no one could know where he was. And no one could follow him because"|FALSE
836|"there was now no carpet to follow on."|FALSE
836|"Jane burst into tears, but Anthea, though pale and frantic, was"|FALSE
836|"dry-eyed."|FALSE
836|"'It MUST be a dream,' she said."|FALSE
836|"'That's what the clergyman said,' remarked Robert forlornly; 'but it"|FALSE
836|"wasn't, and it isn't.'"|FALSE
836|"'But the Lamb never wished,' said Cyril; 'he was only talking Bosh.'"|FALSE
836|"'The carpet understands all speech,' said the Phoenix, 'even Bosh. I"|FALSE
836|"know not this Boshland, but be assured that its tongue is not unknown to"|FALSE
836|"the carpet.'"|FALSE
836|"'Do you mean, then,' said Anthea, in white terror, 'that when he was"|FALSE
