836|"infant,' the Phoenix said calmly."|FALSE
836|"'And WHAT did it mean? Oh WHAT?'"|FALSE
836|"'Unfortunately,' the bird rejoined, 'I never studied Bosh.'"|FALSE
836|"Jane sobbed noisily, but the others were calm with what is sometimes"|FALSE
836|"called the calmness of despair. The Lamb was gone--the Lamb, their own"|FALSE
836|"precious baby brother--who had never in his happy little life been for a"|FALSE
