836|"alone into the great world with no other companion and protector than a"|FALSE
836|"carpet with holes in it. The children had never really understood"|FALSE
836|"before what an enormously big place the world is. And the Lamb might be"|FALSE
836|"anywhere in it!"|FALSE
836|"'And it's no use going to look for him.' Cyril, in flat and wretched"|FALSE
836|"tones, only said what the others were thinking."|FALSE
836|"'Do you wish him to return?' the Phoenix asked; it seemed to speak with"|FALSE
836|"some surprise."|FALSE
836|"'Of course we do!' cried everybody."|FALSE
836|"'Isn't he more trouble than he's worth?' asked the bird doubtfully."|FALSE
836|"'No, no. Oh, we do want him back! We do!'"|FALSE
836|"'Then,' said the wearer of gold plumage, 'if you'll excuse me, I'll just"|FALSE
836|"pop out and see what I can do.'"|FALSE
836|"Cyril flung open the window, and the Phoenix popped out."|FALSE
836|"'Oh, if only mother goes on sleeping! Oh, suppose she wakes up and wants"|FALSE
836|"the Lamb! Oh, suppose the servants come! Stop crying, Jane. It's no"|FALSE
836|"earthly good. No, I'm not crying myself--at least I wasn't till you said"|FALSE
836|"so, and I shouldn't anyway if--if there was any mortal thing we could"|FALSE
836|"do. Oh, oh, oh!'"|FALSE
836|"Cyril and Robert were boys, and boys never cry, of course. Still, the"|FALSE
836|"position was a terrible one, and I do not wonder that they made faces in"|FALSE
836|"their efforts to behave in a really manly way."|FALSE
836|"And at this awful moment mother's bell rang."|FALSE
836|"A breathless stillness held the children. Then Anthea dried her eyes."|FALSE
