836|"once. The time has come when I must leave you.'"|FALSE
836|"All four children breathed forth a long sigh of relief."|FALSE
836|"'We needn't have bothered so about how to break the news to it,'"|FALSE
836|"whispered Cyril."|FALSE
836|"'Ah, sigh not so,' said the bird, gently. 'All meetings end in partings."|FALSE
836|"I must leave you. I have sought to prepare you for this. Ah, do not give"|FALSE
836|"way!'"|FALSE
836|"'Must you really go--so soon?' murmured Anthea. It was what she had"|FALSE
836|"often heard her mother say to calling ladies in the afternoon."|FALSE
836|"'I must, really; thank you so much, dear,' replied the bird, just as"|FALSE
836|"though it had been one of the ladies."|FALSE
836|"'I am weary,' it went on. 'I desire to rest--after all the happenings"|FALSE
836|"of this last moon I do desire really to rest, and I ask of you one last"|FALSE
836|"boon.'"|FALSE
