836|"Now that it had really come to parting with the Phoenix, whose favourite"|FALSE
836|"he had always been, Robert did feel almost as miserable as the Phoenix"|FALSE
836|"thought they all did."|FALSE
836|"'I ask but the relic designed for the rag-and-bottle man. Give me what"|FALSE
836|"is left of the carpet and let me go.'"|FALSE
836|"'Dare we?' said Anthea. 'Would mother mind?'"|FALSE
836|"'I have dared greatly for your sakes,' remarked the bird."|FALSE
836|"'Well, then, we will,' said Robert."|FALSE
836|"The Phoenix fluffed out its feathers joyously."|FALSE
836|"'Nor shall you regret it, children of golden hearts,' it said."|FALSE
836|"'Quick--spread the carpet and leave me alone; but first pile high the"|FALSE
