836|"The Phoenix was walking round and round the egg, clucking with joy and"|FALSE
836|"pride."|FALSE
836|"'I've laid it, you see,' it said, 'and as fine an egg as ever I laid in"|FALSE
836|"all my born days.'"|FALSE
836|"Every one said yes, it was indeed a beauty."|FALSE
836|"The things which the children had bought were now taken out of their"|FALSE
836|"papers and arranged on the table, and when the Phoenix had been"|FALSE
836|"persuaded to leave its egg for a moment and look at the materials for"|FALSE
836|"its last fire it was quite overcome."|FALSE
836|"'Never, never have I had a finer pyre than this will be. You shall not"|FALSE
836|"regret it,' it said, wiping away a golden tear. 'Write quickly: \"Go and"|FALSE
836|"tell the Psammead to fulfil the last wish of the Phoenix, and return"|FALSE
836|"instantly\".'"|FALSE
836|"But Robert wished to be polite and he wrote--"|FALSE
836|"'Please go and ask the Psammead to be so kind as to fulfil the Phoenix's"|FALSE
836|"last wish, and come straight back, if you please.' The paper was pinned"|FALSE
836|"to the carpet, which vanished and returned in the flash of an eye."|FALSE
836|"Then another paper was written ordering the carpet to take the egg"|FALSE
836|"somewhere where it wouldn't be hatched for another two thousand years."|FALSE
836|"The Phoenix tore itself away from its cherished egg, which it watched"|FALSE
836|"with yearning tenderness till, the paper being pinned on, the carpet"|FALSE
836|"hastily rolled itself up round the egg, and both vanished for ever from"|FALSE
836|"the nursery of the house in Camden Town."|FALSE
836|"'Oh, dear! oh, dear! oh, dear!' said everybody."|FALSE
836|"'Bear up,' said the bird; 'do you think _I_ don't suffer, being parted"|FALSE
836|"from my precious new-laid egg like this? Come, conquer your emotions and"|FALSE
836|"build my fire.'"|FALSE
836|"'OH!' cried Robert, suddenly, and wholly breaking down, 'I can't BEAR"|FALSE
836|"you to go!'"|FALSE
836|"The Phoenix perched on his shoulder and rubbed its beak softly against"|FALSE
836|"his ear."|FALSE
836|"'The sorrows of youth soon appear but as dreams,' it said. 'Farewell,"|FALSE
836|"Robert of my heart. I have loved you well.'"|FALSE
836|"The fire had burnt to a red glow. One by one the spices and sweet woods"|FALSE
836|"were laid on it. Some smelt nice and some--the caraway seeds and the"|FALSE
836|"Violettes de Parme sachet among them--smelt worse than you would think"|FALSE
836|"possible."|FALSE
836|"'Farewell, farewell, farewell, farewell!' said the Phoenix, in a"|FALSE
836|"far-away voice."|FALSE
836|"'Oh, GOOD-BYE,' said every one, and now all were in tears."|FALSE
