836|"it."|FALSE
836|"'Whatever have you done with the carpet?' asked mother next day."|FALSE
836|"'We gave it to some one who wanted it very much. The name began with a"|FALSE
836|"P,' said Jane."|FALSE
836|"The others instantly hushed her."|FALSE
836|"'Oh, well, it wasn't worth twopence,' said mother."|FALSE
836|"'The person who began with P said we shouldn't lose by it,' Jane went on"|FALSE
